## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 1401](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1401) imposes Self-Employment Contributions Act (SECA) tax: **12.4 % OASDI** on net SE earnings up to the SSA wage base ($176,100 for 2025) plus **2.9 % Medicare** on all net SE earnings. [§ 1402(a)(12)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1402) reduces the base to **92.35 %** of net SE earnings (the residual approximates the employer-share deduction).

For U.S.-citizen-in-Germany filers, the [U.S.-Germany Totalization Agreement (1979)](https://www.ssa.gov/international/Agreement_Pamphlets/germany.html) keeps SE earnings out of § 1401 when the taxpayer holds a German Certificate of Coverage. The certificate-driven SSA-coverage path is not yet modeled — the law helper fails closed in that case. Schedule SE is the filed form.

